import React from 'react';
import {Icon, Menu, Grid, Image, Button, Divider} from 'semantic-ui-react'
export default class NavbarMenu extends React.Component {

    state = { activeItem: 'wall' }

    handleItemClick = (e, { name }) => this.setState({ activeItem: name })

    render(){
        const { activeItem } = this.state
        return(
            <Menu stackable  pointing inverted size={"massive"}>
                <Menu.Item>
                    <Image
                        src='./../../img/MatchApp-Logo.png'
                        size={"small"}/>
                </Menu.Item>
                <Menu.Menu icon='labeled'>
                    <Menu.Item
                        name='wall'
                        icon='wall'
                        active={activeItem === 'wall'}
                        onClick={this.handleItemClick} >
                        <Icon name='home' />
                        Wall
                    </Menu.Item>
                    <Menu.Item
                        name='Messages'
                        active={activeItem === 'testimonials'}
                        onClick={this.handleItemClick}>
                        <Icon name='conversation' />
                        Messages
                    </Menu.Item>
                </Menu.Menu>
                <Menu.Item
                    name='Notifications'
                    active={activeItem === 'sign-in'}
                    onClick={this.handleItemClick}>
                    <Icon name='bell' />
                    Notifications
                </Menu.Item>
                <Menu.Menu position='right'>
                    <Menu.Item>
                        <Button>Log in</Button>
                    </Menu.Item>
                    <Menu.Item>
                        <Button>Sign up</Button>
                    </Menu.Item>
                </Menu.Menu>
            </Menu>
        )
    }
}
